<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Horseback" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Horseback,</orth> the part of the horse on which its rider sits: <cit><quote>sits on his h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.289" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 289</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>on h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 8</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 85</bibl>. <emph>a h.,</emph> in the same sense: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.378" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 378</bibl>. 387 (M. Edd. <emph>o' h.</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>